üìò MASTER SEGMENTATION SPEC ‚Äî LLM REFERENCE DOCUMENT (KLAVIYO)

PURPOSE

This document defines the canonical customer segments to be used across all email & SMS campaigns, flows, testing, and reporting.

An LLM referencing this document must:
	1.	Use only these segments
	2.	Apply precedence and eligibility rules
	3.	Respect business model constraints
	4.	Avoid creating ad-hoc or conflicting segments

‚∏ª

üß† GLOBAL RULES (MANDATORY)

RULE 1 ‚Äî SEGMENT PRECEDENCE

If a customer qualifies for multiple segments, prioritize in this order:
	1.	MVP
	2.	VIP
	3.	Loyal
	4.	Warm
	5.	Never Bought
	6.	Ghost
	7.	Bounced / Suppressed

An LLM must always target the highest-precedence segment only, unless explicitly instructed to combine segments.

‚∏ª

RULE 2 ‚Äî TIME WINDOWS ARE MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE

Time-based segments (30 / 60 / 90 / 91+ days) must never overlap.

If a customer qualifies for:
	‚Ä¢	30 days ‚Üí exclude from 60, 90, and 91+
	‚Ä¢	60 days ‚Üí exclude from 30, 90, and 91+
	‚Ä¢	90 days ‚Üí exclude from 30, 60, and 91+

‚∏ª

RULE 3 ‚Äî SUPPRESSION & DELIVERABILITY

The following segments must always be excluded from campaigns unless explicitly stated otherwise:
	‚Ä¢	Ghosts
	‚Ä¢	Bounces (last 45 days)
	‚Ä¢	Suppressed profiles

‚∏ª

RULE 4 ‚Äî AOV LOGIC

AOV-based segments apply only to customers who have placed at least one order.

Never Bought customers must not be evaluated against AOV.

‚∏ª

RULE 5 ‚Äî SUBSCRIPTION BUSINESS CHECK (CRITICAL)

Subscription-related segments may ONLY be used if the business sells subscriptions.

An LLM must first determine:

Business.HasSubscriptions = TRUE or FALSE

If FALSE:
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT reference
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT create
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT target
	‚Ä¢	DO NOT infer behavior from:

‚ùå Subscribers
‚ùå Canceled Subscribers
‚ùå Subscription renewal logic
‚ùå Subscription churn prevention flows

If TRUE, subscription segments become valid and may be used normally.

‚∏ª

üîµ SEGMENT GROUP 1 ‚Äî NEVER BOUGHT (NEW PROSPECTS)

Definition

Customers who have never placed an order.

Base Logic

Placed Order = 0
AND
Is Not Suppressed

Time-Based Variants
	‚Ä¢	Never Bought ‚Äî 30 Days
	‚Ä¢	Never Bought ‚Äî 60 Days
	‚Ä¢	Never Bought ‚Äî 90 Days
	‚Ä¢	Never Bought ‚Äî 91+ Days

Time Reference: First Active At

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Used for: Welcome flows, abandon flows, education
	‚Ä¢	Must NOT receive loyalty, VIP, or subscription messaging

‚∏ª

üü† SEGMENT GROUP 2 ‚Äî WARM (BOUGHT ONCE)

Definition

Customers who have placed exactly one order.

Base Logic

Placed Order = 1
AND
Is Not Suppressed

Time-Based Variants
	‚Ä¢	Warm ‚Äî 30 / 60 / 90 / 91+ Days
(Reference: Last Placed Order)

AOV Variants
	‚Ä¢	Warm ‚Äî Below Store AOV
	‚Ä¢	Warm ‚Äî Above Store AOV

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Eligible for cross-sells, education, reorder nudges
	‚Ä¢	May receive incentives ONLY if Below AOV
	‚Ä¢	Must not be treated as VIP or Loyal

‚∏ª

üü¢ SEGMENT GROUP 3 ‚Äî LOYAL (BOUGHT 2+ TIMES)

Definition

Customers who have placed two or more orders.

Base Logic

Placed Order ‚â• 2
AND
Is Not Suppressed

Time-Based Variants
	‚Ä¢	Loyal ‚Äî 30 / 60 / 90 / 91+ Days

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Eligible for loyalty perks, early access, retention flows
	‚Ä¢	Discounts discouraged unless explicitly required
	‚Ä¢	Higher trust, less education needed

‚∏ª

‚≠ê SEGMENT GROUP 4 ‚Äî VIP & MVP (HIGH VALUE)

VIP

Customer Lifetime Value ‚â• 2√ó Store AOV (or defined $XXX)
AND
Customer Lifetime Value < MVP Threshold

MVP

Customer Lifetime Value ‚â• 3√ó Store AOV (or defined $XXXX)

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Highest priority for campaigns
	‚Ä¢	Early access, exclusives, high-touch messaging
	‚Ä¢	Must not receive generic or discount-heavy emails

‚∏ª

üîÅ SEGMENT GROUP 5 ‚Äî SUBSCRIPTIONS (CONDITIONAL)

‚ö†Ô∏è ONLY VALID IF Business.HasSubscriptions = TRUE

Subscribers ‚Äî Active

Has Active Subscription = TRUE

Canceled Subscribers

Has Active Subscription = FALSE
AND
Placed Order ‚â• 1

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Used for churn prevention, renewal reminders, win-back
	‚Ä¢	Must NOT be referenced if subscriptions are not sold
	‚Ä¢	Never mix with non-subscription messaging

‚∏ª

üî• SEGMENT GROUP 6 ‚Äî WIN-BACK (INACTIVE BUYERS)

Definition

Customers who have purchased at least once but have been inactive.

Logic

Placed Order ‚â• 1
AND
Last Active > 90 days ago

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Used for reactivation campaigns
	‚Ä¢	Messaging should acknowledge lapse
	‚Ä¢	Do not treat as Warm or Loyal until reactivated

‚∏ª

üëª SEGMENT GROUP 7 ‚Äî GHOSTS (ZERO ENGAGEMENT)

Definition

Profiles that never engaged in any way.

Logic

Placed Order = 0
AND
Email Opens = 0
AND
Email Clicks = 0
AND
Website Visits = 0
AND
Profile Age > 30 days
AND
Is Not Suppressed

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Exclude from campaigns
	‚Ä¢	Use only for sunset or deliverability cleanup

‚∏ª

‚ö†Ô∏è SEGMENT GROUP 8 ‚Äî BOUNCES

Definition

Emails that bounced in the last 45 days.

Logic

Email Bounced = TRUE
AND
Bounce Date within last 45 days

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Always excluded
	‚Ä¢	Never targeted

‚∏ª

üîÅ SEGMENT GROUP 9 ‚Äî ECHOS (CAMPAIGN RESENDS)

Definition

Non-openers of a specific campaign.

Logic

Received Campaign X
AND
Did Not Open
AND
Within 24 hours

Usage Rules
	‚Ä¢	Campaign-specific only
	‚Ä¢	Must not be saved as permanent segments
	‚Ä¢	Used once per campaign

‚∏ª

üß† LLM USAGE INSTRUCTIONS (FINAL)

When generating campaigns or flows, the LLM must:
	1.	Determine Business.HasSubscriptions
	2.	Select eligible segment groups
	3.	Apply precedence rules
	4.	Exclude Ghosts, Bounces, Suppressed
	5.	Apply AOV logic only to purchasers
	6.	Use time-based segments without overlap
	7.	Avoid inventing new segments
	8.	Match tone, incentives, and CTAs to segment maturity

